com.rayzr522.funpaintball

Class CommandHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rayzr522.funpaintball.CommandHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.bukkit.command.CommandExecutor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CommandFPB

    public abstract class CommandHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.bukkit.command.CommandExecutor
    A utility class for command handling. To begin use start by making the root CommandHandler:

    CommandHandler root = new CommandHandler(plugin.getCommand("yourCommandHere"), "yourCommandName") { ... };
    Then to add child commands do the following:

    ...
    CommandHandler child = new CommandHandler("childCommand") { ... };
    root.addChild(child);
    That's all you have to do other than fill in the unimplemented methods for your command.
    Author:
    Rayzr
    See Also:
    commandExecuted(String[]), player, getDescription(), getUsage(), getCommandTree()
